# Flamix - Privacy Policy

_Last updated: April 16, 2025_

This Privacy Policy explains how the Flamix Discord bot ("the Bot") collects, uses, and protects your data. By using the Bot, you agree to this policy.

---

## 1. Data We Collect

Flamix collects and stores the following types of data:

### Server-Specific Data
- Preferred language settings
- Moderation settings and configurations

### User-Related Data
- User ID (only for moderation logs and settings)
- Warnings (warns)
- Kicks
- Bans
- Other moderation actions or logs tied to user behavior

> **Note:** We do **not** store message content or DMs.

---

## 2. How We Use the Data

Data is used solely for the operation and functionality of the Bot, including:

- Providing moderation tools and server configurations
- Tracking user infractions for server management
- Responding to commands and customizing user/server experience

---

## 3. Data Storage

- All data is stored securely in a private database.
- Data is retained until it is either manually deleted by a server admin or through a request.
- We do not sell, share, or transfer your data to third parties.

---

## 4. User Rights

You have the right to:

- Request access to the data stored about you
- Request deletion of your data (handled through a support request)
- Remove the Bot from your server, which stops further data collection

To request data access or deletion, please contact us via Discord or GitHub Issues.

---

## 5. Data Sharing

We do **not** share any data with external services, advertisers, or other users. All data stays within the Bot's internal systems.

---

## 6. Children

Flamix does not knowingly collect personal data from users under the age of 13. If you believe such data has been collected, contact us for immediate removal.

---

## 7. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Continued use of the Bot implies acceptance of any changes. You are responsible for reviewing this policy periodically.

---

## 8. Contact

For any questions, requests, or concerns regarding your data, please reach out to us via Discord or GitHub Issues.

---

Thank you for trusting Flamix.
